Mojom contract in chrome/browser/slayzone/mojom/layout.mojom mirrors the
shared outer file at packages/shared/mojo-bindings/mojom/layout.mojom —
Phase 4.3 generates TS bindings from the outer copy; this in-tree copy is
what Chromium's mojom() target compiles to C++. Keep the two in sync
(diff is an invariant).

SlayzoneLayoutHost owns a ReceiverSet<LayoutHost>; each region WebUI binds
via Bind(). Methods route to native views: SetRegionVisible →
WebView::SetVisible, FocusRegion → WebView::RequestFocus, SetRegionSize is
advisory today (SplitView is authoritative) and wires real resize in
Phase 7.

Binder registration from chrome://slayzone-* hosts to the per-BrowserView
SlayzoneLayoutHost lands with Phase 7 when the first region consumes the
interface.
